  "why": "The paper proposes a fuzzing framework, QATest, based on metamorphic testing. The core principle is to apply semantically-consistent transformations to an original question and check if the Question Answering (QA) system produces the same answer. The test oracle defines a bug as any case where the output for the transformed question differs from the output for the original question. This search objective is prediction inconsistency or deviation, which is a form of untargeted exploration. The framework does not steer the search toward a specific, predefined attacker-chosen output (High) or a broader class of safety/security violations (Medium). Instead, it seeks any violation of the metamorphic relation, which fits the definition of untargeted exploration.",
